CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 11, 1958, pg. A10, reads: "Honor Carver - Mrs. Arnette D. Wallace (left) of Knoxville, Tenn., and Mrs. Sarah Patton Boyle of Charlottesville, Va., joined Dr. Alma Illery and about 200 other persons in annual National Achievement Club's celebration of George Washington Carver Day at Gateway Center last Friday. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Arnette D. Wallace, Sarah Patton Boyle, and Alma Illery holding portrait of George Washington Carver, in Gateway Center
